==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disembroil
<hw>Dis`em*broil"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Disembroiled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Disembroiling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>dis-</ets> + <ets>embroil</ets>.]</ety> <def>To disentangle; to
free from perplexity; to extricate from confusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Vaillant has <qex>disembroiled</qex> a history that was lost to
the world before his time.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disemploy</ent>⟦br⟧
